    "Examples of interoperability protocols include Polkadot, Cosmos, and Chainlink (ElBahrawy et al. 2017).",
    "These protocols use different approaches to achieve interoperability, such as cross-chain messaging, inter-blockchain communication, and oracle-based solutions.",
    "Another approach is to use interoperability bridges that enable the transfer of value and data between different blockchain networks and systems.",
    "Examples of interoperability bridges include Arkane Network, Wanchain, and Ren (Ray 2023).",
    "Interoperability bridges typically use a two-way pegging mechanism to lock up assets on one blockchain network and release them on another network."
